  "comments": "This coin has been minted with 1771 frozen date until 1784. Three main variant can be described:<br />\r\nKM# 615.1 (1771; Altona Mint) &quot;C&quot; in monogram is 15 mm. high while &quot;7&quot; in monogram is 10 mm. high and have a thick cross bar. Wide crown above monogram. Widely spaced K.M. in value.<br />\r\nKM# 615.2 (1773; Copenhagen Mint) &quot;C&quot; in monogram is 16 mm. high while &quot;7&quot; in monogram is 9 mm. high and have a thin cross bar. Wide crown above monogram. Widely spaced K.M. in value.<br />\r\nKM# 615.3 (1784; Copenhagen Mint) &quot;C&quot; in monogram is 17 mm. high while &quot;7&quot; in monogram is 12 mm. high. Small but higher crown above thin monogram. Less spaced K.M. in value.",
